238,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d1107818-Reviews-or235-Holland_Inn-London_England.html#REVIEWS,"Holland Inn Reviews, London",Probably the tiniest room I've ever stayed in ...,"The hotel is close to an Underground station (Kensington Olympia) but the service is infrequent. Kensington High St station is a better option. The rooms are really tiny - clean enough but impossible to move around in. This is a hotel for sleeping only; really it was like being in a cupboard! Breakfast is very basic but again, the breakfast room so small that only about 10 people could squeeze in. The worst feature is the noisy street. Holland Road is like a racetrack at night, and even with the window closed, the noise is bad. It is impossible to leave it open. There is a bright sign over the front door which also lights up the rooms on that side. Internet access costs 5 pounds (flat fee) and works well. There are very basic tea and coffee facilities in the room. I stayed for‚Ä¶",Date of stay: May 2009,2.0
