241,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d1107818-Reviews-or240-Holland_Inn-London_England.html#REVIEWS,"Holland Inn Reviews, London","Spotlessly clean, but rooms are tiny.","Friendly courteous staff and management. Mine was a single room on a budget and I stayed three nights. I'd have liked somewhere to put clothes and stuff but there was neither wardrobe nor chest of drawers. There was, however, a good-sized fridge, a safe, an air-conditioning unit and a good quality television receiving many channels. The en-suite facility worked but the shower drain was slow and the water level crept alarmingly towards the room level. Generally, it's a decent place if you don't mind compromising on comforts and, as the title says, it really is spotlessly clean.",Date of stay: February 2009,4.0
